International Trade and Industry MinisterHajime Tamura told a parliamentary session Japan's small- andmedium-sized enterprises are seriously suffering from the yen'srise and can only stand levels around 170 yen.    He also said he still believes a dollar exchange rate levelplus or minus 10 yen from 170 yen would be within levels agreedupon last month in Paris by six major industrial nations.Finance ministers of Britain, Canada, France, Japan, the U.S.And West Germany agreed on February 22 to cooperate instabilizing exchange rates around the current levels. Thedollar had closed here at 153.77 yen on February 20. REUTER&#3;